text: FCR 2001 Duisburg (officially known as Fußballclub Rumeln 2001 Duisburg) was a German women's association football club that was dissolved in 2013 because of a financial crisis. After the club disbanded, it merged with MSV Duisburg. == Notable players == Some notable players who played for the club include Alexandra Popp, Ashlyn Harris, Sara Däbritz, Simone Laudehr, Lieke Martens and Annike Krahn. == Honours == * Bundesliga 1: 2000 * DFB-Pokal 3: 1998, 2009, 2010 * UEFA Cup 1: 2009 Category:2001 establishments in Germany Category:Duisburg Category:Football clubs in North Rhine-Westphalia Category:Women's football clubs Category:2013 disestablishments in Europe Category:2010s disestablishments in Germany
title: FCR 2001 Duisburg
